由 Hamilton 原理

$$\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\delta T - \delta V{\rm{ + }}\delta {W_{nc}}{\rm{d}}t} = 0$$

考虑动能

$$
T = \int_0^L {\frac{1}{2}m\left( x \right){{\left( {\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}} \right)}^2}{\rm{d}}x}
$$

则有

$$
\begin{array}{l}
\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\delta T{\rm{d}}t} \\
{\rm{ = }}\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\delta \left( \int_0^L {\frac{1}{2}m\left( x \right){{\left( {\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}} \right)}^2}{\rm{d}}x} \right) {\rm{d}}t} \\
{\rm{ = }}\int_0^L {\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {m\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}\delta \left( {\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}} \right){\rm{d}}t} {\rm{d}}x} \\
 =\int_0^L \left ( \left. {m\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}\delta w\left( {x,t} \right)} \right|_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} - \int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {m\left( x \right)\frac{{{\partial ^2}w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial {t^2}}}\delta w\left( {x,t} \right){\rm{d}}t} \right) {\rm{d}}x\\
= - \int_0^L {\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {m\left( x \right)\frac{{{\partial ^2}w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial {t^2}}}\delta w\left( {x,t} \right){\rm{d}}t} {\rm{d}}x}
\end{array}
$$

势能

$$
V = \int_0^L {\frac{1}{2}EI\left( x \right){{\left( {\frac{{{\partial ^2}w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial {x^2}}}} \right)}^2}{\rm{d}}x}
$$

则有

$$
\begin{align*}
\int_{t_1}^{t_2} \delta V \, dt = &amp; \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \delta \left( \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} EI(x) \left( \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right)^2 dx \right) dt \\
= &amp; \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \delta \left( \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) dx \right) dt \\
= &amp; \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \left. \left[ EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \delta \left( \frac{\partial w(x,t)}{\partial x} \right) \right] \right|_0^L \right. \\
&amp; - \left.\int_0^L \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) \delta \left( \frac{\partial w(x,t)}{\partial x} \right) dx
 \right) dt \\
= &amp; \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \left. \left[ EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \delta \left( \frac{\partial w(x,t)}{\partial x} \right) \right] \right|_0^L \right. \\
&amp; - \left. \left[ \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) \delta w(x,t) \right] \right|_0^L \\
&amp; \left. + \int_0^L \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) \delta w(x,t) dx \right) dt 
\end{align*}
$$

非保守力做功

$$\delta {W_{nc}} = \int_0^L {f\left( {x,t} \right)\delta w\left( {x,t} \right){\rm{d}}x}
$$

则有

$$
\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\delta {W_{nc}}{\rm{d}}t} = \int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\int_0^L {f\left( {x,t} \right)\delta w\left( {x,t} \right){\rm{d}}x} {\rm{d}}t}
$$

所以

$$
\begin{align*}
\int_{t_1}^{t_2} &amp;\left( \int_0^L \left( -m(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial t^2} - \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) + f(x,t) \right) \delta w(x,t) \, dx \right. \\
&amp;\left. - \left. \left[ EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \delta \left( \frac{\partial w(x,t)}{\partial x} \right) \right] \right|_0^L \right. \\
&amp;\left. + \left. \left[ \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) \delta w(x,t) \right] \right|_0^L \right) \, dt = 0
\end{align*}
$$

依据题目有


考虑 $x = 0$时,

$$
\delta w(0,t) = 0, EI(x) \left. \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right|_{x=0} =0
$$

考虑 $x = L$时,

$$
EI(x) \left. \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right|_{x=L} = 0, EI(x) \left. \frac{\partial^3 w(x,t)}{\partial x^3} \right|_{x=L} = 0
$$

方程有

$$
m(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial t^2} + \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) = f(x,t)
$$"><h2>1.1</h2><p>由 Hamilton 原理</p><p></p><div class="MathJax" display="block" style="text-align:center;"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="25.205ex" height="5.731ex" role="img" 知$f(x, t) = 0$,假定$m, EI$常定

所以

$$
m(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial t^2} + \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) = 0
$$

令$w\left( {x,t} \right) = W\left( x \right){e^{i\omega t}}$

则有

$$\frac{{d^4 W(x)}}{{dx^4}} - \frac{{m \omega^2}}{{EI}} W(x) = 0$$

解为

$$W(x) = A \cos\left(\alpha x\right) + B \sin\left(\alpha x\right) + C \cosh\left(\alpha x\right) + D \sinh\left(\alpha x\right)$$
则有

$$\frac{{d^4 W(x)}}{{dx^4}} - \frac{{m \omega^2}}{{EI}} W(x) = 0$$

解为

$$W(x) = A \cos\left(\alpha x\right) + B \sin\left(\alpha x\right) + C \cosh\left(\alpha x\right) + D \sinh\left(\alpha x\right)$$

其中，$\alpha = \left(\frac{m\omega^2}{EI}\right)^{\frac{1}{4}}$ 

代入边界条件则有

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; -1 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\
-\sin(\alpha L) &amp; -\cos(\alpha L) &amp; \sinh(\alpha L) &amp; \cosh(\alpha L) \\
-\cos(\alpha L) &amp; \sin(\alpha L) &amp; \cosh(\alpha L) &amp; \sinh(\alpha L)
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
A \\
B \\
C \\
D
\end{bmatrix} = 0
$$

容易发现

$$B = D = 0$$

根据行列式为0

$$
\begin{vmatrix}
-\sin(\alpha L) &amp; \sinh(\alpha L) \\
-\cos(\alpha L) &amp; \cosh(\alpha L) 
\end{vmatrix} = 0
$$

即

$$\sin (x) \cosh (x)-\cos (x) \sinh (x) = 0$$

解得

$${\alpha _0}L = 0,\;\;{\alpha _1}L \approx 3.927,\;\;{\alpha _2}L \approx 7.069,{\rm{ }}{\alpha _3}L \approx 10.210,\;\;{\alpha _1}L \approx 13.352$$

将$\alpha L$代入可解得

$$
\begin{align*}
W_0(x) &amp;= kx \\
W_i(x) &amp;= \sin(\alpha_i x) + \frac{\sin(\alpha_i L)}{\sinh(\alpha_i L)}\sinh(\alpha_i x), \quad i = 1,2,3
\end{align*}
$$"><h2>1.2</h2><p>知<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="10.27ex" height="2.262ex" role="img" focusable="false" viewBox="0 -750 4539.2 1000" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" ## 1.1

由 Hamilton 原理

$$\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\delta T - \delta V{\rm{ + }}\delta {W_{nc}}{\rm{d}}t} = 0$$

考虑动能

$$
T = \int_0^L {\frac{1}{2}m\left( x \right){{\left( {\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}} \right)}^2}{\rm{d}}x}
$$

则有

$$
\begin{array}{l}
\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\delta T{\rm{d}}t} \\
{\rm{ = }}\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\delta \left( \int_0^L {\frac{1}{2}m\left( x \right){{\left( {\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}} \right)}^2}{\rm{d}}x} \right) {\rm{d}}t} \\
{\rm{ = }}\int_0^L {\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {m\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}\delta \left( {\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}} \right){\rm{d}}t} {\rm{d}}x} \\
=\int_0^L \left ( \left. {m\left( x \right)\frac{{\partial w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial t}}\delta w\left( {x,t} \right)} \right|_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} - \int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {m\left( x \right)\frac{{{\partial ^2}w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial {t^2}}}\delta w\left( {x,t} \right){\rm{d}}t} \right) {\rm{d}}x\\
= - \int_0^L {\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {m\left( x \right)\frac{{{\partial ^2}w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial {t^2}}}\delta w\left( {x,t} \right){\rm{d}}t} {\rm{d}}x}
\end{array}
$$

势能

$$
V = \int_0^L {\frac{1}{2}EI\left( x \right){{\left( {\frac{{{\partial ^2}w\left( {x,t} \right)}}{{\partial {x^2}}}} \right)}^2}{\rm{d}}x}
$$

则有

$$
\begin{align*}
\int_{t_1}^{t_2} \delta V \, dt = & \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \delta \left( \int_0^L \frac{1}{2} EI(x) \left( \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right)^2 dx \right) dt \\
= & \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \int_0^L EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \delta \left( \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) dx \right) dt \\
= & \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \left. \left[ EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \delta \left( \frac{\partial w(x,t)}{\partial x} \right) \right] \right|_0^L \right. \\
& - \left.\int_0^L \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) \delta \left( \frac{\partial w(x,t)}{\partial x} \right) dx
\right) dt \\
= & \int_{t_1}^{t_2} \left( \left. \left[ EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \delta \left( \frac{\partial w(x,t)}{\partial x} \right) \right] \right|_0^L \right. \\
& - \left. \left[ \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) \delta w(x,t) \right] \right|_0^L \\
& \left. + \int_0^L \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) \delta w(x,t) dx \right) dt
\end{align*}
$$

非保守力做功

$$\delta {W_{nc}} = \int_0^L {f\left( {x,t} \right)\delta w\left( {x,t} \right){\rm{d}}x}
$$

则有

$$
\int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\delta {W_{nc}}{\rm{d}}t} = \int_{{t_1}}^{{t_2}} {\int_0^L {f\left( {x,t} \right)\delta w\left( {x,t} \right){\rm{d}}x} {\rm{d}}t}
$$

所以

$$
\begin{align*}
\int_{t_1}^{t_2} &\left( \int_0^L \left( -m(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial t^2} - \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) + f(x,t) \right) \delta w(x,t) \, dx \right. \\
&\left. - \left. \left[ EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \delta \left( \frac{\partial w(x,t)}{\partial x} \right) \right] \right|_0^L \right. \\
&\left. + \left. \left[ \frac{\partial}{\partial x} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) \delta w(x,t) \right] \right|_0^L \right) \, dt = 0
\end{align*}
$$

依据题目有


考虑 $x = 0$时,

$$
\delta w(0,t) = 0, EI(x) \left. \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right|_{x=0} =0
$$

考虑 $x = L$时,

$$
EI(x) \left. \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right|_{x=L} = 0, EI(x) \left. \frac{\partial^3 w(x,t)}{\partial x^3} \right|_{x=L} = 0
$$

方程有

$$
m(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial t^2} + \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) = f(x,t)
$$

## 1.2

知$f(x, t) = 0$,假定$m, EI$常定

所以

$$
m(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial t^2} + \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2} \left( EI(x) \frac{\partial^2 w(x,t)}{\partial x^2} \right) = 0
$$

令$w\left( {x,t} \right) = W\left( x \right){e^{i\omega t}}$

则有

$$\frac{{d^4 W(x)}}{{dx^4}} - \frac{{m \omega^2}}{{EI}} W(x) = 0$$

解为

$$W(x) = A \cos\left(\alpha x\right) + B \sin\left(\alpha x\right) + C \cosh\left(\alpha x\right) + D \sinh\left(\alpha x\right)$$
则有

$$\frac{{d^4 W(x)}}{{dx^4}} - \frac{{m \omega^2}}{{EI}} W(x) = 0$$

解为

$$W(x) = A \cos\left(\alpha x\right) + B \sin\left(\alpha x\right) + C \cosh\left(\alpha x\right) + D \sinh\left(\alpha x\right)$$

其中，$\alpha = \left(\frac{m\omega^2}{EI}\right)^{\frac{1}{4}}$

代入边界条件则有

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 1 & 0 & 1 \\
0 & -1 & 0 & 1 \\
-\sin(\alpha L) & -\cos(\alpha L) & \sinh(\alpha L) & \cosh(\alpha L) \\
-\cos(\alpha L) & \sin(\alpha L) & \cosh(\alpha L) & \sinh(\alpha L)
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
A \\
B \\
C \\
D
\end{bmatrix} = 0
$$

容易发现

$$B = D = 0$$

根据行列式为0

$$
\begin{vmatrix}
-\sin(\alpha L) & \sinh(\alpha L) \\
-\cos(\alpha L) & \cosh(\alpha L)
\end{vmatrix} = 0
$$

即

$$\sin (x) \cosh (x)-\cos (x) \sinh (x) = 0$$

解得

$${\alpha _0}L = 0,\;\;{\alpha _1}L \approx 3.927,\;\;{\alpha _2}L \approx 7.069,{\rm{ }}{\alpha _3}L \approx 10.210,\;\;{\alpha _1}L \approx 13.352$$

将$\alpha L$代入可解得

$$
\begin{align*}
W_0(x) &= kx \\
W_i(x) &= \sin(\alpha_i x) + \frac{\sin(\alpha_i L)}{\sinh(\alpha_i L)}\sinh(\alpha_i x), \quad i = 1,2,3
\end{align*}
$$
